%N A070740 Order of the subgroup of the symmetric group S_(2n) generated by the 2 cycles: (1,2,...n,2n,2n-1,...,n+1) and (1,2,...,2n).
%H A070740 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A070740/b070740.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..100</a>
%F A070740 If n is even: a(n) = (2n)!.
%F A070740 If n is congruent to 1 mod 4: a(n) = (n!)^2 / 2.
%F A070740 If n is congruent to 3 mod 4: a(n) = (n!)^2.
%t A070740 a[n_] := Switch[Mod[n, 4], 0, (2*n)!, 1, (n!)^2 / 2, 2, (2*n)!, 3, (n!)^2]; Array[a, 20, 2] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 12 2025 *)
%o A070740 (PARI) a(n) = if(n < 2, 0, if(n%2==0, (2*n)!, (n!)^2 / if(n%4==1, 2, 1))); \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 04 2018
